Purpose defamation? Ústí zoo is looking for a new veterinarian, no one is interested
Most recently at the end of this month. The city's management attributed this to the rumors that swarmed around the zoo's former director and veterinarian, Václav Poživil, that he purposely killed exotic animals that he cared for. For example, it was a female Zamba rhinoceros, Kala the elephant or Snuňák the orangutan.
The city council therefore announced a new contract. "For veterinary care for the zoo with an estimated value of performance of 3.5 million crowns excluding VAT and for the city's Center for Animals in Need with an estimated value of performance of 2.8 million crowns excluding VAT," said Romana Macová, the city's spokesperson.
Deputy Mayor Věra Nechybová (UFO) explained that the city was announcing a competition for veterinary services for the third time. "Dr. Poživil had to explain the unfounded suspicions. I consider it a blatant defamation of such a high-quality expert," she said.
Experts specializing in exotic animals are very few in number. "It's certainly not pleasant. The zoo provides veterinary care in the form of orders," she said. Orders and contracts cost the same money. "The garden must comply with the Public Procurement Act in terms of funding," explained zoo spokesperson Nikola Roštejnská.
Václav Poživil himself is one of the recognized experts. For example, he participated in a unique operation in which the cheetah Jane was the world's first cheetah to receive a total prosthesis. He served as the zoo's director from 2009 to 2012. He did not comment on the anonymous rumors about himself. Yesterday he did not receive phone calls or respond to text messages.
As for the contract for the zoo, some veterinarians believe that in zero interest there is not necessarily a fear of similar purposeful allegations, as in his case, but simply little information. For example, veterinarian Jiří Král has not heard of it. "This is the first I've heard from you. No one has approached us. I think such a thing will spread quickly," he added.
