Those who move in a divided society and don't want to go completely crazy, will welcome situations where they don't have to root for their own. When they can give the benefits to those they otherwise criticize. If only to avoid feeling that they are oriented only by pre-assigned labels. Such situations include the list of badly damaged monuments that President Zeman fences during his favorite trips to the regions.
