Přindiš, Prskavec and Fišerová safely advanced to the semi-finals of the World Championships
Kayakers Vít Přindiš and Jiří Prskavec as well as canoeist Tereza Fišerová safely advanced to the semi-finals of the Canoe Slalom World Championships in Seu d'Urgell. Přindiš was fourth in Friday's qualification, Prskavec fifth and Fišerová eighth. The other three Czech representatives will be in Spain seeking a semi-final start in the afternoon corrective qualifying run.
Among the strong representative group of kayakers, Vavřinec Hradilek did not succeed, receiving a 50-second penalty at the start of the run for an incorrect pass. On the other hand, Přindiš and Prskavec can relax and concentrate on Sunday's semi-finals.
"I set myself a goal to go down to 30 on the first run, which I did. Not that I didn't care how I ended up, because on Sunday the start is very early in the morning, so I was hoping to be a bit higher to have a better starting position," said Přindiš, praising the well-being in Seu. "Before the watch race I felt the worst in the 14 days we've been here. But then the race was good and today it was better. It's beautiful all the time, nice races here, the spectators came, so fine," he smiled.
Prskavec was also happy. "In qualifying you don't want to make an unnecessary mistake. In the first gates it didn't quite work. Then I did the middle very well, without any problems and I knew I had the mileage, so there was a second mistake when I wanted to go straight down and I turned the erk. Overall I can't be dissatisfied. The form is, we'll see how it goes," said this year's overall World Cup winner.
Both representatives praised going to the start at the end of the semi-final block on Sunday. "I'm not a morning person, it's also cold here in the morning, and when you're here at eight, you want to wear a jacket and a sweatshirt," said Přindiš. "Overall, the semi-final lasts an hour and a half, which is quite a good difference from the point of view of sleep," agreed Prskavec.
Of the three Czech singcanoeists, only Fišerová succeeded, Eva Říhová finished two places behind the advancing 20, Kateřina Havlíčková was 35. "I went down the top part as expected, in the middle part I felt like I wasn't following and wasn't going according to plan, but I managed to get into the comfortable track I wanted to ride. I made two shots and I'm just behind the winner with a clean time. I have a good starting position for the semi-finals," Fišerová said.
