10. Acceptance Procedure, Delivery Upgrade to Acceptance Procedure
10.1 The aim of the Acceptance Procedure is to verify that the result of the Contractor's activity matches the Specification and Amendment Documentation of the Changes included in the Upgrade Supply. Furthermore, the aim of the Acceptance Procedure is to verify that the Incidents included in the Upgrade Supply are resolved.
10.2 The formalities and steps of the Acceptance Procedure are listed in Annex No. 9 (Acceptance Procedure). The Acceptance Procedure includes acceptance criteria that the Upgrade Supply must meet.
10.3 If the Contractor demonstrates to the Customer the result of its activities under this Agreement and demonstrates the results of the unit and integration tests it has performed on such result, the Contractor shall submit the result of its activities to the Customer for performance of the Acceptance Procedure.
10.4 The Parties shall draw up an entry on the submission of the result of the Contractor's activities to the Acceptance Procedure. The Contractor shall submit a draft of the Upgrade Supply to the Acceptance Procedure. The draft of the Upgrade Supply to the Acceptance Procedure shall always contain the result of the unit and integration tests. The specimen of the Upgrade Supply to the Acceptance Procedure is contained in Appendix 10 (specimen of the Upgrade Supply to the Acceptance Procedure).
11. Start, progress and termination of the Acceptance Procedure of the Upgrade Supply
11.1 Without undue delay, after the Parties sign the Upgrade Supply to the Acceptance Procedure, they shall agree on a timetable for performance of the Acceptance Procedure and the Customer shall initiate the Acceptance Procedure.
11.2 During the execution of the Acceptance Procedure, the Customer draws up Incidents that have manifested themselves in the outcome of the Contractor's activity, in comparison with the required features of the Supplies Upgrade, and delivers this inventory to the Contractor. Incidents may be reported by the Customer to the Contractor during the execution of the Acceptance Procedure. During the Acceptance Procedure, the Contractor may resolve Incidents, correct defects and, in accordance with the agreed procedures, deliver the corrected outcome of its activity to the Customer for further execution of the Acceptance Procedure.
11.3 The Acceptance Procedure is completed either:
11.3.1 by performing all steps of the Acceptance Procedure, resolving all reported Incidents and removing all identified defects of the Supplies Upgrade; or
11.3.2 by ending the period that specifies the agreed time schedule for the execution of the Acceptance Procedure; or
11.3.3 if, during the execution of the Acceptance Procedure, the number of Incidents that are defects exceeds the number of defects listed in the Acceptance Criteria that gives the Customer the right to stop the Acceptance Procedure.
12. Successful completion of the Acceptance Procedure of the Delivery Upgrade
12.1 If all steps of the Acceptance Procedure have been performed, and if the Delivery Upgrade meets all of the Acceptance Criteria listed in Appendix 9 (Acceptance Procedure), and if, by the end of the Acceptance Procedure, the Supplier has resolved all reported Incidents of its Result and removed all identified defects of its Result, the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as a success without reservation.
12.2 If all the steps of the Acceptance Procedure have been completed, and if the Delivery Upgrade meets all the acceptance criteria listed in Appendix 9 (Acceptance Procedure), and if, by the end of the Acceptance Procedure, the Supplier has not resolved all the reported Incidents of the result of its activity and has not eliminated all the identified defects of the result of its activity, the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as a success with reservation.
12.3 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as a success, the Parties shall draw up a Record of acceptance of the Delivery Upgrade into use. The Supplier shall submit a draft Record of acceptance of the Delivery Upgrade into use. If the Delivery Upgrade has defects, the draft Record of acceptance shall always include a list of defects and the required date for their removal. No later than one (1) week from the date on which the Customer agreed with the draft Record of acceptance of the Delivery Upgrade into use, the Parties shall sign the Record of acceptance. A sample of such record of acceptance of the Delivery Upgrade into use shall form Appendix 11 (Model of the Record of acceptance of the Delivery Upgrade into use).
12.4 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as a success subject to the removal of defects, the Contractor shall remove all defects within the dates specified in the Notice of Acceptance of Supply Upgrade in Use. The corrected Supply shall be handed over by the Contractor to the Customer for re-verification. If the Contractor does not remove all defects within the dates specified in the Notice of Acceptance of Supply Upgrade in Use, the Contractor shall be in default.
12.5 By signing the Notice of Acceptance of Supply Upgrade in Use (1) the Customer confirms that at the time of signing such Notice, Supply Upgrade does not have defects that prevent the use of the Application; and (2) the Contractor declares that Supply Upgrade is performed in accordance with the Specification and Amendment Documentation of the Changes included in the Upgrade and the Czech legal order. The moment at which the last Party signs the Notice of Acceptance of Supply Upgrade in Use is the moment at which (1) the Contractor has fulfilled its obligation to perform the Supply; and (2) the Customer acquires ownership of the Supply.
12.6 Even if the Customer is in default of taking over the Delivery Upgrade, the Contractor does not have the right to sell the Delivery Upgrade to a third party. If the Customer takes over the Delivery Upgrade, the rights from the obvious defect of the Delivery Upgrade remain with the Customer, even if the Contractor objects to the Court that the right has not been exercised in time.
13. Failed termination of the Acceptance Procedure of the Delivery Upgrade
13.1 If the Delivery Upgrade does not meet the acceptance criteria listed in Appendix 9 (Acceptance Procedure), the Acceptance Procedure shall be terminated as a failure. The Acceptance Procedure shall also be terminated as a failure if, in the course of performing the Acceptance Procedure, the number of defects identified by the Customer exceeds the number of defects listed in the acceptance criteria, which gives the Customer the right to stop the Acceptance Procedure. If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as a failure, the Customer shall write down the defects that have occurred to perform the Acceptance Procedure submitted to the Delivery Upgrade, and return this inventory, together with the Delivery Upgrade, to the Contractor.
13.2 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as unsuccessful, the Contractor shall be deemed not to have submitted the Delivery Upgrade to perform the Acceptance Procedure. The relevant Record of the Delivery Upgrade to perform the Acceptance Procedure shall be deemed never to have occurred.
13.3 If the Delivery Upgrade The Contractor does not submit the Delivery Upgrade to perform the Acceptance Procedure on time, the Contractor shall be in default.
13.4 If the Acceptance Procedure is terminated as unsuccessful, the Contractor shall remove the defects that led to the termination of the Acceptance Procedure as unsuccessful within the shortest possible time and shall deliver the corrected Delivery to the Customer to perform the repeated Acceptance Procedure. The costs of performing the repeated Acceptance Procedure shall be borne by the Contractor.
