Appendix 6 / Project Management Methodology
1. Project Charter
1.1 The purpose of the Project Charter is to define the formal management processes and the method of communication between the parties for the purpose of fulfilling the subject of the Contract, so that the performance of the work or the provision of services is in accordance with the Contract and this Project Management Methodology. The Project Charter makes available to those involved in the execution of the work or the provision of services those parts of the Contract that are necessary for the execution of its object. The Project Charter specifies the occupation of the project's organizational structure, the method of communication, the control and escalation mechanisms and the structure of the Project Portal, where all documentation related to the execution of the work or the provision of services is archived. The Project Charter is prepared by the Project Leaders and approved by the Steering Commitee Initial Meeting.
2. Project Organizational Structure
2.1 The Project Organizational Components are (1) Project Steering Committee (SCP) and (2) Project Leadership (PVP) and (3) Working Teams. SCP and PVP are the permanent organizational components of the project. Working Teams are the temporary organizational components of the project.
3. Steering Committee
3.1 Competences of the SCP / Steering Committee of the Project in particular:
3.1.1 Approves the Project Charter; and
3.1.2 Addresses escalated issues that have not been resolved at the PVP level; and
3.1.3 Addresses issues with an impact on the scope of the work performed or the services provided; and
3.1.4 Addresses issues related to the delivery schedule; and
3.1.5 Addresses issues related to the remuneration or structure of the remuneration for the services provided or the work performed; and
3.1.6 Accepts individual supplies, services, parts of the work or the work as a whole; and
3.2 Members of the SCP / For the Customer, the members of the SCP are (1) the Project Sponsor for Business and (2) the ISIT Division Director and (3) the Project Manager. For the Contractor, the members of the SCP are (1) the Management Representative and (2) the Project Manager.
3.3 The SCP / SCP Meeting meets at least quarterly. The exact dates on which the SCP meets regularly are determined by the Project Manager in the Project Charter. The SCP always meets to assess a significant milestone of the delivery schedule (e.g. the start or end of the acceptance procedure). The SCP always meets when a Project Manager calls for a SCP meeting. The SCP meets at the Customer's headquarters.
3.4 The agenda of the SCP/SCP meeting and the documents to be discussed shall be delivered to the SCP members by the Project Leader on behalf of the Contractor at least 3 working days before the SCP meeting. At its meeting, the SCP shall always discuss the status report of the project and draft minutes relating to the acceptance of the supply, services or work.
3.5 Right to invite experts and advisors / If a Party deems it necessary, it shall have the right to invite experts or advisors to the meeting of the SCP, but shall inform the other Party beforehand, stating the reasons why the presence of experts or advisors at the SCP meeting is expedient.
3.6 Voting / After discussing each item on the agenda, the SCP members shall vote on the proposal that is submitted to the relevant item on the agenda. Each SCP member shall have one vote.
3.7 SCP Decisions with Impact on Contractual Terms / If the SCP's decision relates to the contractual terms under which the work is performed or the services provided, in particular if the SCP's decision has an impact on the remuneration for which the work is performed or the services provided, the Customer shall, without undue delay after the adoption of such a decision, prepare an amendment to the contract in question.
3.8 Minutes / From the SCP meeting, the Project Manager shall prepare the minutes for the Customer, which shall be delivered to the Project Manager on behalf of the Contractor.
4. Project Leadership
4.1. Competences of the SCP / Project Leadership in particular:
4.1.1. Controls all outputs of the various stages of the performance of the work or the provision of services; and
4.1.2. Evaluates and refines the timing of deliveries and the progress of work in the performance of the work or the provision of services; and
4.1.3. Discusses changes that do not affect the text of the Contract; and
4.1.4. Controls the interaction between the Customer and the Contractor; and
4.1.5. Controls the risks and remedial actions related to the performance of the work or the provision of services; and
4.1.6 escalates at the SCP meeting.
4.2 Members of the SCP / For the Client are members of the SCP (1) the Project Manager and (2) the Principal Business Analyst and (3) the Application Architect. For the Contractor the members of the SCP are (1) the Project Manager and (2) the Principal Analyst and (3) the Principal Architect.
4.3 The SCP / SCP meeting meets once a week, at the Client's headquarters or in the form of remote communication.
4.4 Agenda of the SCP meeting and supporting documents / Agenda of the SCP meeting and supporting documents to be discussed will be delivered to the members of the SCP by the Project Manager for the Contractor at least 1 working day before the meeting of the SCP. At its meeting, the SCP always discusses:
4.4.1 the fulfilment of open tasks from previous SCP; and
4.4.2 the progress of performance of the work or provision of services; and
4.4.3 the fulfilment and updating of the schedule of works; and
4.4.4 identified problems and how to resolve them; and
4.4.5 the plan of the next step; and
4.4.6 the risks related to performance of the work or provision of services; and
4.4.7 the evaluation and other requirements for the Client's cooperation; and
