Annex 12 / Safety rules
1. Definitions of terms
1.1. For the purposes of this Annex, the following terms and phrases shall have the meanings set out below:
A security incident means any breach of the confidentiality, integrity or availability of Information Assets.
An information asset means any information, process, hardware or software component that (1) supports the business activities of the Eligible Entity, or (2) has a value to the Eligible Entity, or (3) whose disclosure, unauthorized change or unavailability has a negative impact on the Eligible Entity.
Persons of the Contractor means persons who are directly or indirectly involved in the fulfilment of the subject of this Agreement, including persons of subcontractors of the Contractor.
The Eligible Entity environment means the premises where the Eligible Entity carries out its business activities and the information and communication systems used by the Eligible Entity and containing Information Assets.
2. Personnel safety
2.1 None of the Persons of the Contractor:
2.1.1 has no criminal record;
2.1.2 has not been convicted of an intentional criminal offence in the past and is not being prosecuted at the time of fulfilment of the subject of this Agreement;
2.2 If the Contractor detects in the Persons of the Contractor a non-compliance with the above rules, it must immediately inform the Customer. The Customer is entitled to require that such person does not further participate in the execution of the work arising from the subject of this Agreement, either directly or indirectly, and is entitled to require the Contractor to provide adequate compensation.
2.3 The Contractor provides the Customer with a complete list of the Persons of the Contractor. The Contractor undertakes to inform the Customer in advance of changes in the personnel security of fulfilment of this Agreement.
2.4 Persons of the Contractor:
2.4.1 must be acquainted with these security rules;
2.4.2 have all necessary examinations and attestations that result from the law or the regulator's requirements for the type of work they are to perform in connection with fulfilment of this Agreement;
2.4.3 are regular training in the areas of information security by the Contractor.
2.5 Persons of the Contractor must not enter the environment of the Entitled Entity under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances or bring weapons, explosives, flammable substances, fighting equipment, poisons, radioactive and toxic substances, or any other substances threatening human life and/or health.
3. Physical security
3.1 Access of Persons of the Contractor to the environment of the Entitled Entity is allowed only if their presence is necessary for the performance of the work obligations arising from this Agreement.
3.2 Persons of the Contractor are always accompanied by a responsible employee of the Customer in the environment of the Entitled Entity.
3.3 Free movement of Persons of the Contractor in the environment of the Entitled Entity is allowed only if a personal access card has been issued to the person. Person of the Contractor must not further lend the access card to third parties or allow third parties access to the environment of the Entitled Entity.
3.4 In case of loss of the access card or in case of suspected loss of the access card, the Supplier is obliged to inform the Customer without delay.
3.5 Without undue delay after the completion of the works arising from this Agreement or after the termination of this Agreement, or if further physical access of the Supplier's Persons to the Entitled Entity's Environment is no longer necessary, the Customer shall ensure that all the Supplier's Persons return the borrowed access cards to the Customer.
3.6 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Supplier's Person may not remove any Information Assets from the Entitled Entity's Environment via the storage medium.
4. Identification and authentication of the Supplier's Persons in the Entitled Entity's Environment
4.1 The Supplier's Persons are assigned only accounts allowing unambiguous identification of the user and only with such authorizations as they absolutely need to perform their work obligations arising from this Agreement.
4.2 The Contractor performs normal work tasks under non-privileged accounts, using accounts with administrator's permissions only if necessary.
4.3 The Contractor's Persons may not access the Internet if they work under an account with administrator's permissions or with applications running under administrator's permissions.
4.4 The Contractor's Inactive Persons Accounts are proactively reported by the Contractor to the Customer.
4.5 Shared Accounts are used by the Contractor only with the Customer's prior written consent.
4.6 In case of password disclosure or suspicion of password disclosure, the Contractor must immediately ensure that the password is changed or blocked.
5. Certificate Handling
5.1 Access to certificates (both logical and physical) will only be granted to those Contractor's Persons for whom such access is necessary for the performance of their work obligations.
5.2 The Contractor's Persons may not provide or make certificates available to third parties without the written consent of the Customer.
5.3 After their installation, certificates may only be stored in secure storage in places where their storage is necessary for the performance of this Agreement, and any other copies shall be destroyed in a way that makes their recovery impossible.
5.4 If possible, the private key of the certificate must be set as non-exportable. The private key of the certificate must always be protected by a strong password and must not be stored in unencrypted form.
5.5 The Contractor undertakes to inform the Customer immediately of the loss or suspected loss of confidentiality of the private key of the certificate.
6. Information Assets Handling
6.1 Work with Information Assets is limited only to places that exclude the observation of sensitive information by unauthorized persons. Specifically, it is forbidden to work with Information Assets in mass transport vehicles, in public places and in places where there is a risk of observation from industrial cameras.
6.2 Upon completion of the work arising from this Contract, the Contractor shall without undue delay return or remove all Information Assets stored in the environment of the Contractor, unless the possession of such information is required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to electronic and paper documentation. The removal of Information Assets must be done in a way that makes it impossible to restore them again.
6.3 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not grant access to Information Assets to any third parties who are not authorized to participate in the performance of this Contract.
6.4 The Contractor is obliged to ensure adequate security of the computer technology on which Information Assets are stored, processed or transmitted. In relation to Information Assets, the Contractor shall ensure that in the environment of the Contractor:
6.4.1 tools are used to encrypt disks, folders or files in order to exclude unauthorized access to Information Assets,
6.4.2 tools are used for detecting and removing malicious code with settings for periodic update of the database of malicious code signatures with a frequency not exceeding one week; and adequate processes for monitoring, logging and responding to a positive finding of malicious code are set up;
6.4.3 processes for updating security patches of software components are defined, set up, executed and monitored at an interval not exceeding one month from the release of the patches;
6.4.4 the Internet environment is separated by a firewall, which is connected to the surveillance; and the Contractor's Persons use exclusively encrypted VPN connections for remote access to prevent unauthorised interception and change of transmitted communications.
6.5 If the Information Assets are transmitted by the Contractor outside the premises of the Authorised Entity, the Contractor shall be required to ensure the physical security of these assets and keep these Information Assets under constant supervision. The Contractor is obliged to comply with the safety and operational instructions of the manufacturer of the hardware on which the Information Assets are processed.
7. Work in the Environment of the Entitled Entity
7.1 The Contractor is obliged to acquaint himself with and act in accordance with the Classification of Information Assets standard if the Customer provides it.
7.2 For hardware that is owned and managed by the Customer or hardware that, including its configuration, has been approved in advance by the Customer, the Contractor may not make unauthorized changes to the configuration of this hardware by the Customer. In particular, the Contractor may not make changes to the security configuration of the hardware. For each hardware thus installed, the process of applying security patches must be explicitly and formally stipulated, including responsibilities arising from roles within the process.
7.3 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not install or run any software previously unauthorized by the Customer.
7.4 Without the written consent of the Contractor, the Contractor shall not be authorized to perform any physical or logical security testing or any type of inspection mechanisms of the Entitled Entity.
7.5 The Contractor shall not manipulate audit records in any way.
7.6 Persons of the Contractor shall not be authorized to work with software, hardware or data content that is not directly related to the performance of this Agreement.
7.7 Persons of the Contractor shall not perform any activities detrimental to other natural or legal persons, including the sending of unsolicited emails, the sending of fraudulent emails, the distribution of malicious code or participation in attacks in order to disable the availability of services.
7.8 All actions performed by Persons of the Contractor The Contractor shall log and keep a record of them for 3 years.
7.9 Without the written consent of the Contractor, Persons of the Contractor shall not connect their own storage devices to any Computing Device of the Entitled Entity.
7.10 At the provided workplace, the Contractor's Persons are obliged to ensure during the period of physical absence:
7.10.1 cleanliness and order so that the workplace can be used safely;
7.10.2 adequate physical security of all Information Assets;
7.10.3 logical locking of access to Information Assets so that unauthorized access to these Information Assets cannot occur.
7.11 The Contractor's Persons are not entitled to install devices enabling remote interception or to make any audio or video recording without the prior written consent of the Customer.
8. Crisis management
8.1 The Contractor's Persons are obliged to prevent, to the extent possible, the occurrence of crisis situations (e.g. fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations in which personal injury or damage to the Entitled Person's property could occur.
8.2 In the event of a crisis situation, the Person of the Contractor who is physically present at the event site is obliged, without exception and without delay, to comply with the regulations and directives applicable in the given locality and to obey the instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies to the case of exercises.
8.3 In the event of crisis management, the Person of the Contractor is obliged to obey the instructions of the Crisis Manager of the Contractor without delay.
9. Reporting security incidents
9.1 If the Contractor identifies a security incident, he is obliged to report it without delay to the tool https://helpdesk.jtfg.com (phone: +420 221 710 911).
