The Prague Stock Exchange closed the trading week with a slight rise. The PX index rose 0.13 percent to 1038.45 points. It was driven by Czech banks, the telecommunications company O2 and the technology company Avast. On the other hand, Austrian titles and the media company CME did not do well. This is the result of trading on the exchange's website.
