Young Czechs think they are good with money. Survey does not confirm this
"So it turns out that young Czechs have somewhat more confidence in their knowledge of finance than is the reality. In this case, women and respondents without a high school diploma had a significantly greater share of the wrong answers," said KRUK director Jaroslava Palendalová.
Men and young high school or university students are more likely to believe in their knowledge of financial products.
Young Czechs learn the most about the functioning of financial matters from their parents (37 percent), by self-study on the Internet (23 percent) and only in the third row from teaching at school (21 percent).
Women are the main ones who consult with their parents about financial issues, while men are the ones who look for information on the Internet. Getting information about finances from their parents predominates at all ages of young people, regardless of their educational attainment or personal income. Prospects from financial institutions, professional magazines and publications have practically minimal influence.
"Once again, the importance of raising children by their parents, who represent the authority in all major areas of life, is becoming apparent. This is why the level of financial literacy of parents, who pass on their knowledge and experience to their offspring, is crucial," said Palendalová.
Savings and investments are preferred by 94 percent of young people.
Clearly, young people are on the question of whether it is better to save and buy, for example, your own house or flat, or to enjoy and spend money, without savings and own housing.
The strategy of saving and investing in long-term tangible assets is followed by 94 percent of respondents. This is true across all age categories of young people, regardless of their educational attainment, social status or current level of personal income.
The strategy of saving is then 100 percent espoused by people married with two or more children and employees in the public sector. Instead, people living alone and with an income of more than CZK 30,000 per month are more likely to enjoy themselves.
