Toyota boss Takeshi Uchiyamada confirmed at an international conference on hydrogen that a new generation will arrive next year. Toyota still believes that these cars have a future and within ten years they will match the price of hybrids. Of course, this is linked to the development of petrol networks. But the future is connected with hydrogen as much as with electricity.
At the conference, the word hydrogen was often used to refer to the needs of ecological operation not of passenger cars but on the contrary of large tractors, ships, trains, etc. Simply those means of transport that need to cover long distances in one refuel. Purely battery-powered versions cannot offer that. Toyota could thus find new outlets thanks to its great experience and long development.
It remains to be remembered that, like Toyota, Hyundai, which now also offers the Nexo hydrogen crossover, believes in hydrogen propulsion.
