"The intention is to maintain stable rents in Berlin and to give tenants security," Berlin Mayor Michael Müller (SPD) said in a statement. "At the same time, we will continue to build new flats and legally treat the rent freeze," he added. Municipal firm Gewobag will take over the thousands of flats located in the Spandau and Reinickendorf neighborhoods in the western part of the city this December.
